commitResults.messageTitle: Add grade level field to Person
commitResults.messageBody:
The user, who is piano teacher in Singapore, does not have a way to
check the grade level of the students, while doing so would benefit
them by featuring additional data.

Add grade level to Person to allow the user to store the grade level

The commit not only includes the addition of the grade level field to
the Person class, but also the necessary changes to the commands,
parsers, and storage classes to support the new field. The commit also
includes the necessary changes to the UI to display the grade level.

Additionally, the commit modifies User Guide to include the new field
and its usage.

Let's add the grade level field to the Person class to allow the user
to store the grade level of the students.

commitResults.messageBody:
KeyContacts does not support searching by fields. This feature is
useful for users who want to search for students by specific fields
such as name, phone number, address, and grade level.

This feature will allow users to search for students by specific fields,
for better usability and flexibility to user.

Implement search by fields feature:
- Add FindStudentDescriptorBuilder in FindCommand as static class to
model variable search fields
- Add StudentDescriptorMatchesPredicate to decide if a student matches
- Update FindCommandParser to support parsing search by fields
- Update respective testing classes to support testing of search by
fields
- Update UserGuide.md to include documentation for search by fields

Let's implement search by fields feature to improve usability and
flexibility to user.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'search_fields' of https://github.com/zzawook/tp into sort_by_field
Add sort command to sort students by field(s)
commitResults.messageBody:
The application does not support sorting functionality.

This feature is crucial for users when they want to view the
student listed in a particular order.

Add a sort command to allow users to sort the students by
field(s) in ascending or descending order.

The sort command will be able to sort the students by the
following fields:
- name
- phone
- address
- grade level

In the process of implementation, the ModelManager was modified
to return a sorted list of students instead of filtered list,
and filter to always be followed by the sort.

Let's add the sort command to the application.
